Function1
1. Selected Functionality
I've chosen to test Freeplane's core node folding/unfolding functionality, which has been created for:
Fold nodes to hide child nodes
Unfold nodes to reveal child nodes
Recursively fold/unfold entire subtrees

2.FSM Diagram

3.Test Cases
Test Case 1: Basic Fold/Unfold Path
Test Item
Description
Test Case ID
FOLD-01
Type of Test
Black-box Testing (GUI Functional Test)
Path Tested
S1 → S2 → S1
Purpose
Verify basic node folding and unfolding functionality
Prerequisite
1. Freeplane installed and running
2. Parent node with children created
Input Data
1. Parent node containing child nodes
2. Mouse click events
Steps
1. Click fold icon (E1) on fully expanded node (S1)
2. Verify node enters folded state (S2), child nodes invisible
3. Click unfold icon (E2) on folded node (S2)
4. Verify node returns to fully expanded state (S1), all children visible
Expected Result
Node correctly toggles between expanded and folded states
Actual Result
[To be filled after execution]
Status
[Pass/Fail]

